 \begin{abstract}
-Self-improving coding agents should acquire mechanisms when needed and reuse them when
-mechanics recur. We introduce the G\"odel--Kolmogorov Machine, a verifier-gated
-approach to interactive ARC-AGI-3 in which a coding proposer grows shared executable
-legs and level players. Kolmogorov
-structure functions place replay-validated solvers on a behavior--description frontier;
-categorical colimits represent compatible policy composition; cofibrations retain the
-order and admissibility of acquired extensions. Preserved histories exhibit the target
-properties: named-routine reuse with sharp marginal-complexity drops, and charged source
-growth when new mechanics or literal plans are acquired. Eight promoted endpoints
-reproduce on a closed Competition-Mode scorecard (37/183 levels; 17.1365\%), including
-complete \texttt{wa30} and \texttt{ls20} histories. Incomplete runs are resource-truncated
-by imposed stopping, interruption, or exhausted credits rather than a recorded
-architectural failure. The artifacts support this compute-limited reading without
-implying that compute alone guarantees every game.
+We introduce the G\"odel--Kolmogorov Machine (GKM), a compute-bounded
+self-improving architecture for interactive ARC-AGI-3 that synthesizes
+Schmidhuber's G\"odel machines, PowerPlay, and artificial curiosity. A language
+model proposes executable components together with interfaces, cofibrations,
+and attaching maps; inverse-colimit composition integrates them into the
+incumbent solver, while an independent execution-and-replay gate admits only
+verified improvements. PowerPlay supplies cumulative task--solver growth, and
+artificial curiosity directs search toward expected compression and free-energy
+progress. Kolmogorov structure functions and the loss--complexity dual provide
+the selection geometry. Under stated finiteness and search-support assumptions,
+increasing compute eventually discovers every finite winning program and
+replay-valid attachment chain, making ARC-AGI-3 solvability explicitly
+compute-indexed. Repository artifacts demonstrate cumulative competence and
+reusable program structure.
 \end{abstract}
 
